{
  "stem": "2684.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was in 1945, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] August.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Approximately August.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there I met a lot of Hungarian Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Ladies who were there, and Jews, and they were all much better condition than where we were.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know where they were during this-- the years of the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there we had the football game.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After there, we had dinner, and we got the things and we went back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then we went into Munich.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And one end of the Munich, I don't know what how they call it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was another lager in the city, and they had, it's like a hangar as well.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And also we went there, and we met other [NON-ENGLISH], and that's how our social life started slowly and slowly.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in Auschwitz I was together with a lot of political prisoners-- communists, Hungarian communists-- who was prisoned by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was together with the former Hungarian Army Minister.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His name was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Germans deported him because he broke all the rules that he brought the Jews back from the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because he said that without guns they cannot serve the country, so why they are in Russia?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the Germans deported him to Dachau, the same like they did to us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I got freed with him, and I was in the same wagon with him when we went back to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was also together with a gentleman who became the president of the-- he formed the association in Dachau who looked after our interest towards the Americans and who-- and towards the Germans, like a committee.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And his name was Szegedy-Maszak Aladar, and he became the first ambassador-- Hungarian Ambassador to America.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
